---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import EmailCapture from '../components/EmailCapture.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="RevAudio is a small plugin shop building tools around mechanical metaphors. High quality, simple controls, built to feel."
>
  <section class="plugin-detail">
    <div class="container" data-reveal>
      <h1>About RevAudio</h1>
      <p class="pitch">
        RevAudio is a small plugin shop. We build mixing and mastering tools around
        mechanical metaphors &mdash; cars, gauges, AC dashboards, suspensions &mdash;
        because the tactile, physical world is a better teacher than another menu.
      </p>

      <h2>Three values</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Quality.</strong> Every DSP stage is measured, null-tested, and audited.
        We use a custom test bench (Pit Stop) that produces machine-readable measurements
        for every build before it ships.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Simplicity.</strong> A producer in the middle of a session should glance
        at a panel and know what it does. Fewer knobs, more decisions.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Creativity.</strong> Tools that move people emotionally. We optimise for
        feel, not feature lists.
      </p>

      <h2>How we build</h2>
      <p>
        Every plugin is measured, null-tested, and benchmarked before it ships, then
        regression-tested between releases. Available as VST3, AU, and AAX on Windows and macOS.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Press, partnership, or hello: <a href="/contact">drop a line</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <EmailCapture />
</BaseLayout>
